<Author>TravelFan_01
<Content>Fabulous stay My husband and I chose this hotel after extensive research both on here, other travel sites and personal experiences and we were absolutely not disappointed.The hotel itself has a superb location on Hong Kong Island- it's attached to Pacific Place with it's numerous upmarket shops and lovely restaurants which in turn, houses the Admiralty MTR stop. We found its proximity to the MTR invaluable for our 3 night stay. The Star Ferry was also a 10 minute stroll away which was very handy too.We had booked a Harbour view room which in itself didn't disappoint although the harbour was shrouded in smog for our entire stay which was a shame. Check in was efficient and swift, and we were soon in our room which was extremely spacious, beautifully presented and immaculately kept. It had everything that a deluxe hotel should- electronic safe, bathrobes, iron and board, tea and coffee making facilites, free local newspaper etc as well as bottled water every day and a bowl of fruit and a pot of Chinese tea as a welcome which arrived almost instantly as we arrived in the room as did our cases which were brought up extremely promptly. The bathroom was beautiful- light and airy as well as having the perk of having a small TV set into the wall next to the bath. However, I used the seperate shower there most of the time instead, which was excellent. The only slight negative I can think of in the room was that the mattress was a little firm for me personally. However, it didn't cause me any discomfort in any way and if that is the only negative point I could find, then that says great things about this place.We ate in the hotel's Summer Palace restaurant on our first night and the food was exquisite. Being fans of Chinese food, we know the difference between good and bad and although it was pricier than some other options in Hong Kong, we felt the money was well justified. We also had tea and cakes in Island Gourmet which was also lovely. We didn't have breakfast in the hotel as it wasn't included in our room rate and we were busy on tours and days out during our stay so didn't really have the time.The staff in the hotel were all delightful and couldn't do enough to make our stay pleasurable.All in all, a really fantastic stay in a terrific hotel in a superb city. Staying anywhere else in Hong Kong next time apart from Island Shangri-La, won't even be crossing my mind. 
